Attributes.description: The fundamentals of analysis of lumped linear time-invariant circuits; network theorems; operational amplifiers; first order circuits; DC analysis of diodes, BJT, and FET circuits.
Attributes.prereq: Pre-reqs: MATH 101 and one of PHYS 108, PHYS 118, PHYS 158.
Attributes.coreq: Co-reqs: One of MATH 255, MATH 256, MATH 265.
